author: @lleiou0723
text: Hi, I am new to AWS and I have a silly question (to which I cannot find the answer on the Internet...), how did you turn your terminal with the  [ec2-user@xxxxxx]  headings? Thank you very much!

author: @FranciscoCostaHideOut
text: Hi! Those 'drw...etc' aren't files, they are permissions. In this case they are describing the permissions of the current folder '.', the previous folder '..' and the files in the current folder. http://www.linux.com/learn/tutorials/309527-understanding-linux-file-permissions Cheers, and thanks for the video
